reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 21, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This simple stand securely holds my Starlink Router in my 5th Wheel RV. My router clips into the stand at three locations (the bottom and on either side about a 3rd of the way up) while resting on a solid bottom and back. The cuts for the power and satellite cable are perfect and well positioned. I am impressed with the holding strength to avoid accidental bumps that might knock the router over. I have this installed in my storage bay under the RV. I wanted to get the router off the storage bay floor and out of the way since I am constantly pulling and pushing bins and other items around in the bay (don't want to damage the router). Now it is up high, out of the way, and secure. I am not yet confident it could hold the router in place during travel days, but the ease of removing for storage then clipping into place when ready to use is great.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Fits well, works as intended
reviews.reviewText: Fits my Starlink router well and allows me to raise the height of the router so I can get a better signal out of my house and into my non windowed metal building about 100 feet away. Signal wise, it's not a game changer, but for a minimum investment the added height does provide a better signal inside my shop so it's worth the cost to me. Comes with screws and anchors.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for my RV.
reviews.reviewText: I mounted this in the underbelly or as the manufacturer calls it the basement. of my 5th wheeler, it is directly under the living area aka my office.Perfect for getting the Starlink unit off the floor.The wall bracket it well made and the fitment was perfect, The modem snapped into place after being mounted.The installation was a snap using the supplied hardware. In all, it took me more time to crawl into the basement than it took to install the wall bracket.Because of its location, I did add 2 screw in eyelets and a small bungee to keep it in place when moving my rig. I am not concerned about it falling out of the bracket but again given the location, better to take a bit of extra protection.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to install, easy to use, perfect fit
reviews.reviewText: Recently integrating Starlink into our OB van for live TV alongside a LiveU system, we needed a practical solution to securely mount the router/PSU in a semi-permanent manner, allowing easy removal when required, considering potential separate use from the van. After some searching, I stumbled upon this mount—it fixes in place with screws, offering exceptional stability while also allowing effortless removal of the router when needed.This mount effectively secures the router, providing a strong grip while remaining easily detachable. There isn't much else to add except that this product performs admirably. I wholeheartedly recommend it for anyone seeking a reliable wall-mounting solution for their Starlink router in diverse scenarios.
